      <div class=" clearFloats bigBox"><div class="h2Container gradientHeaderContainer"><h2 class="brownBackground"><a href="/work/quotes/232965-in-stahlgewittern">Quotes from Storm of Steel</a></h2></div><div class="bigBoxBody"><div class="bigBoxContent containerWithHeaderContent">
          <div class="stacked" tyle="padding-bottom:15px">
            <span class="readable">&ldquo;Habent sua fata libelli et balli [Books and bullets have their own destinies]&rdquo;</span>
            <nobr>
              &mdash;
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/quotes/40731-habent-sua-fata-libelli-et-balli-books-and-bullets-have">40 likes</a>
            </nobr>
            <div class="clear"></div>
          </div>
          <div class="stacked" tyle="padding-bottom:15px">
            <span class="readable">&ldquo;Throughout the war, it was always my endeavour to view my opponent without animus, and to form an opinion of him as a man on the basis of the courage he showed. I would always try and seek him out in combat and kill him, and I expected nothing else from him. But never did I entertain mean thoughts of him. When prisoners fell into my hands, later on, I felt responsible for their safety, and would always do everything in my power for them.<br /><br />p. 58&rdquo;</span>
            <nobr>
              &mdash;
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/quotes/1197531-throughout-the-war-it-was-always-my-endeavour-to-view">15 likes</a>
            </nobr>
